headline: RSG Q4 Deep Dive: Margin Discipline and Technology Offset Volume Pressures
summary: Waste management company Republic Services (NYSE:RSG) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 2.2% year on year to $4.14 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $17.1 billion at the midpoint came in 1.3% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.76 per share was 7.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
